  "summary": "Moderate: 389-ds-base security update",
  "details": "389 Directory Server is an LDAP version 3 (LDAPv3) compliant server. The base packages include the Lightweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) server and command-line utilities for server administration.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* 389-ds-base: Malformed userPassword hash may cause Denial of Service (CVE-2024-5953)\n* 389-ds-base: unauthenticated user can trigger a DoS by sending a specific extended search request (CVE-2024-6237)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
